%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Finsider-today%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20daily%20newsletter%20here%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US%20manufacturing%20industry%20is%20at%20a%20crossroads%3A%20try%20catching%20the%20leaders%20where%20they%20are%20or%20beat%20them%20to%20where%20the%20industry%20is%20headed.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEdward%20Mehr%20sits%20firmly%20in%20the%20second%20camp.%20The%20thesis%20of%20his%20robotics-enabled%20manufacturing%20startup%2C%20Machina%20Labs%2C%20is%20that%20America's%20reindustrialization%20needs%20to%20be%20distributed%20and%20flexible.%20Trying%20to%20build%20the%20centralized%2C%20traditional%20factories%20China%20has%20perfected%20is%20a%20lost%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20miracle%20to%20catch%20up%20if%20you%20want%20to%20replicate%20what%20they%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehr%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20not%20the%20right%20chess%20move.%20We%20need%20to%20try%20to%20see%20if%20we%20can%20leapfrog%20and%20then%20do%20the%20next%20generation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20robotics%20in%20factories.%20Mehr%20said%20the%20industry%20is%20still%20five%20years%20away%20from%20a%20major%2C%20ChatGPT-like%20breakthrough.%20But%20there's%20no%20shortage%20of%20companies%20giving%20it%20a%20go%2C%20including%20giants%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-tech-company-elon-musk-ai-robotics-optimus-robotaxi-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-robotics-tye-brady-ai-warehouse-jobs-human-common-sense-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20opportunity%20is%20huge%2C%20with%20the%20manufacturing%20industry%20accounting%20for%20trillions%20of%20dollars.%20It's%20also%20a%20brutal%20business%20to%20break%20into.%20If%20a%20robot%20doesn't%20immediately%20help%20you%20cut%20costs%20or%20improve%20efficiencies%2C%20there's%20not%20much%20point%20pursuing%20it%20any%20further.%20(Example%3A%20Amazon's%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-pulls-plug-blue-jay-warehouse-robot-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BBlue%20Jay%26quot%3B%20warehouse%20robot%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMachina%20Labs%2C%20which%20specializes%20in%20producing%20complex%20metal%20structures%20for%20the%20defense%2C%20aerospace%2C%20and%20automotive%20industries%2C%20sees%20its%20value-add%20on%20two%20fronts.%20Its%20robots%20can%20switch%20between%20different%20manufacturing%20operations%2C%20saving%20the%20time%20it%20would%20take%20to%20retool%20a%20factory%20to%20produce%20a%20new%20product.%20It's%20also%20portable%2C%20meaning%20there's%20no%20need%20to%20custom-design%20factories%20for%20specific%20productions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20is%20crowded%2C%20and%20Mehr%20acknowledged%20that%20competitors%20are%20also%20pursuing%20portability%20or%20flexibility%2C%20but%20typically%20not%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20almost%20rethinking%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20manufacturing%20processes%20from%20scratch%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20to%20our%20factory%2C%20things%20are%20being%20built%20in%20a%20way%20that%20you%20cannot%20see%20in%20any%20other%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20many%20robotics%20players%2C%20Machina%20Labs%20now%20needs%20to%20prove%20its%20thesis%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20raised%20a%20%24124%20million%20Series%20C%20round%20earlier%20this%20month%20from%20investors%20including%20Lockheed%20Martin%20Ventures%20and%20Toyota's%20venture%20arm.%20It'll%20use%20that%20cash%20to%20build%20a%20new%20200%2C000-square-foot%20factory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20factory%20will%20feature%2050%20robots%20and%20initially%20serve%20Lockheed%20Martin.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20produce%20a%20few%20thousand%20structures%20every%20year.%20That's%20a%20significant%20step%20up%20from%20its%20current%20factory%2C%20which%20runs%2010%20robots%20and%20has%20an%20annual%20production%20of%20a%20few%20hundred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20about%20the%20humans%3F%20Tensions%20are%20already%20high%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatt-shumer-viral-essay-scientists-ai-leaders-respond-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI's%20impact%20on%20white-collar%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Are%20blue-collar%20workers%20headed%20to%20a%20similar%20fate%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMachina%20Labs'%20new%20factory%20will%20include%20about%20150%20human%20workers%2C%20which%20Mehr%20said%20is%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20number%20of%20humans%20who'd%20work%20at%20a%20robot-free%20factory.%20The%20work%20is%20different%2C%20but%20no%20one%20seems%20to%20be%20complaining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMehr%20said%20a%20recent%20internal%20survey%20found%20that%20employees'%20interest%20level%20in%20the%20job%20was%20exceptionally%20high.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-fatigue-burnout-software-engineer-essay-siddhant-khare-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESo%20much%20for%20AI%20fatigue%3C%2Fa%3E!)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20working%20with%20robots.%20You're%20working%20with%20software.%20Compared%20to%20previously%2C%20you%20had%20these%20instructions.%20You'd%20follow%20it%20daily%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20you%20almost%20feel%20like%20you're%20playing%20a%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-robotics-could-upend-the-us-manufacturing-industry-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insid