0emerged%20as%20a%20major%20talent%2C%20highlighting%20both%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20potential%20and%20the%20need%20for%20better%20support%20and%20sponsorship%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22JYOTIRMOY%20HALDER%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20oncology%20student%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20cancer%20in%20her%2020s%20after%20spotting%202%20subtle%20symptoms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20flexing%20and%20smiling%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%20during%20cancer%20treatment.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69973772a645d1188189980c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOncology%20researcher%20LaShae%20Rolle%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20cancer%2C%20and%20said%20her%20powerlifting%20background%20helped%20her%20stay%20strong%20during%20treatment.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20LaShae%20Rolle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Ph.D.%20student%20researching%20cancer%20noticed%20she%20had%202%20major%20warning%20signs%20herself%2C%20and%20got%20checked%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20cancer%20at%2026%2C%20and%20now%20advocates%20for%20other%20young%20patients.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20background%20in%20competitive%20powerlifting%20helped%20her%20stay%20strong%20throughout%20treatment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ph.D.%20student%20LaShae%20Rolle%20felt%20a%20pain%20in%20her%20chest%2C%20she%20didn't%20think%20much%20of%20it%20at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20little%20soreness%20made%20sense%3A%20she%20was%20working%20hard%20in%20the%20gym%2C%20preparing%20to%20bench%20press%20nearly%20300%20pounds%20for%20a%20powerlifting%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pain%20came%20and%20went%2C%20but%20then%20Rolle%20noticed%20a%20lump%20in%20her%20breast%2C%20a%20textbook%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreast-cancer-signs-symptoms-lump-nipple-discharge-pain-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewarning%20sign%20of%20breast%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20a%20red%20flag%20she%20was%20deeply%20familiar%20with%20from%20her%20own%20studies%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foncologist-breast-cancer-tips-how-to-reduce-lower-risk-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecancer%20prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2026%2C%20Rolle%20never%20expected%20to%20live%20through%20it%20herself.%20She%20had%20no%20family%20history%20of%20the%20disease%20and%20no%20genetic%20risk%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20took%20her%20symptoms%20seriously.%20She%20scheduled%20a%20check-up%20and%20mammogram%20for%20peace%20of%20mind.%20When%20the%20results%20came%20back%2C%20she%20and%20the%20medical%20technicians%20were%20shocked%20to%20discover%20it%20was%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20not%20on%20my%20radar.%20I%20only%20did%20it%20to%20check%20the%20box%20so%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20regrets%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Rolle%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2028%2C%20Rolle%20said%20she's%20working%20to%20raise%20awareness%20about%20cancer%20screenings%20for%20young%20patients%20who%20may%20not%20even%20realize%20they're%20sick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20reason%20I%20was%20able%20to%20recognize%20the%20signs%20early%20on%20is%20because%20of%20my%20background%20being%20in%20a%20lab%20learning%20about%20cancer%20control%20and%20prevention%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20grateful%3B%20not%20everybody%20knows.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276292546-ec87-4bfd-b2c2-232cd34b542d%5C%22%3EUnique%20challenges%20for%20young%20cancer%20patients%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20certain%20cancers%20were%20rarely%20diagnosed%20in%20younger%20patients.%20The%20median%20age%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foncologist-diagnosed-breast-cancer-no-symptoms-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreast%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%2062%2C%20and%20for%20people%20without%20a%20genetic%20risk%20or%20family%20history%20of%20the%20disease%2C%20preventive%20screenings%20don't%20start%20until%20the%20age%20of%2040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20patients%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s%20are%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20cancer%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20big%20problem%20for%20the%20healthcare%20industry%2C%20accustomed%20mainly%20to%20treating%20very%20young%20or%20older%20patients%2C%20to%20tackle%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-so-many-young-people-getting-colon-cancer-answer-infancy-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly-onset%20cancer%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERolle%20said%20she%20saw%20this%20firsthand%20at%20the%20cancer%20center%20where%20she%20underwent%20treatment.%20In%20the%20waiting%20room%2C%20she%20was%20the%20youngest%20patient%20by%20decades.%20When%20her%20mom%20accompanied%20Rolle%20to%20appointments%2C%20the%20medical%20staff%20assumed%20her%20mother%20was%20the%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20of%20breast%20cancer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERolle%20experienced%20two%20red%20flags%20that%20prompted%20her%20to%20get%20screened%20for%20breast%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPain%20in%20the%20chest%20area%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELump%20in%20the%20breast%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20warning%20signs%20include%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESkin%20irritation%20on%20or%20around%20the%20breasts%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENipple%20discharge%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20to%20the%20size%20or%20shape%20of%20the%20breasts%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20intensely%20isolating%20experience%2C%20Rolle%20said%2C%20compounded%20by%20having%20to%20postpone%20some%20major%20exams%20for%20her%20Ph.D.%20After%20struggling%20to%20find%20peers%20she%20could%20relate%20to%2C%20Rolle%20said%20an%20app%20called%20Cancer%20Buddy%20helped%20her%20connect%20with%20patients%20of%20a%20similar%20age%20and%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20community%20of%20young%20patients%20was%20key%20to%20dealing%20with%20the%20distinct%20challenges%20of%20treatment%20in%20her%2020s%2C%20Rolle%20said%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20burden%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rush%20for%20fertility%20preservation%2C%20and%20the%20shattered%20illusion%20of%20youthful%20invincibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20hard%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20young%2C%20because%20we%20think%20nothing%20can%20happen%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Rolle%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20just%20come%20to%20grips%20with%20what%20is%20your%20reality%20right%20now%20and%20find%20ways%20to%20accept%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ced9ed45-535c-4858-b47f-c83bebd3b16f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20out%20to%20fight%20cancer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20shock%20of%20the%20diagnosis%2C%20Rolle%20saw%20a%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20put%20everything%20she%20had%20studied%20into%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20pursued%20oncology%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-cancer-risk-daily-vigorous-exercise-carrying-shopping-study-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estave%20off%20disease%20with%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20diet.%20In%20fact%2C%20one%20of%20the%20first%20questions%20she%20asked%20her%20Ph.D.%20mentor%20was%20about%20whether%20cancer%20patients%20should%20work%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20been%20lifting%20since%20college%2C%20where%20she%20hit%20the%20gym%20during%20basketball%20training%2C%20but%20decided%20she%20preferred%20lifting%20heavy%20to%20running%20up%20and%20down%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22772%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20deadlifting%20a%20heavy%20barbell.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699737d7f8731049f3af65fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22970%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERolle%20kept%20up%20with%20powerlifting%20exercises%20during%20cancer%20treatment%2C%20and%20wrote%20a%20case%20study%20on%20her%20workout%20regimen.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20LaShae%20Rolle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20she%20became%20the%20patient%2C%20Rolle%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20giving%20up%20weightlifting%20even%20during%20treatment.%20Guidelines%20suggest%20light%20exercise%20can%20help%20cancer%20patients%2C%20but%20don't%20say%20much%20about%20intense%20workouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20there%20wasn't%20much%20information%20on%20what%20she%20should%20do%2C%20Rolle%20researched%20and%20wrote%20it%20herself.%20She%20published%20her%20experience%20in%202025%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Flim2.70034%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecase%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20of%20its%20kind%20to%20analyze%20elite%20powerlifting%20during%20chemotherapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWant%20to%20share%20your%20experience%20with%20cancer%20symptoms%2C%20diagnosis%2C%20or%20treatment%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aglandsverk%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGabrialle%20Landsverk.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERolle%20used%20everything%20she%20knew%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowerlifting-doctor-shares-exercises-build-muscle-longevity-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebenefits%20of%20weight%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20combined%20with%20conditioning%20exercise%20like%20biking%2C%20to%20make%20exercise%20a%20part%20of%20her%20plan%20to%20recovery%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20treatment%2C%20including%20surgeries%2C%20she%20maintained%20about%2090%25%20of%20her%20strength%20and%20said%20that%20being%20an%20athlete%20helped%20her%20meet%20the%20challenge%20head-on.%20It%20even%20prompted%20the%20doctors%20she%20spoke%20with%20to%20start%20recommending%20more%20exercise%20to%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20completely%20changed%20the%20way%20I%20did%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Rolle%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I%20would've%20had%20the%20confidence%20to%20do%20this%2C%20nor%20the%20expertise%20in%20this%20area%20to%20even%20try%20something%20like%20this.%20It's%20crazy%20when%20I%20look%20back%20at%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222376%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20standing%20on%20a%20podium%20with%20a%20medal%20and%20award%20during%20a%20powerlifting%20meet.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69973831a645d11881899829%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221782%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERolle%20won%20awards%20in%20powerlifting%20and%20said%20she%20retained%2090%25%20of%20her%20strength%20during%20chemo%20and%20surgeries.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20LaShae%20Rolle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERolle%20completed%20her%20cancer%20treatment%20in%20October%202024%20and%20is%20in%20remission.%20Her%20recent%20scans%20continue%20to%20come%20back%20clear.%20She%20still%20takes%20medication%20and%20hormone%20therapy%2C%20and%20will%20do%20so%20for%20the%20next%20eight%20years%20to%20stay%20cancer-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Rolle%20is%20back%20on%20track%20to%20graduate%20with%20her%20Ph.D.%20this%20spring.%20She's%20still%20lifting%20heavy%2C%20thinking%20about%20