3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20CEO%20of%20Gap's%20brand%20Mark%20Breitbard%20said%20he%20aims%20to%20make%20meetings%20more%20efficient%20by%20following%203%20rules.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBreitbard%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20question%20default%20meetings%20and%20keep%20the%20invite%20list%20tight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExecutives%20at%20Meta%20and%20Snowflake%20have%20also%20spoken%20recently%20about%20trimming%20superfluous%20meetings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20of%20hyper-efficiency%2C%20leaders%20are%20taking%20a%20close%20look%20at%20the%20meetings%20on%20their%20calendars%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Gap's%20CEO%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20returning%20to%20lead%20Gap's%20global%20brand%20in%202020%2C%20CEO%20Mark%20Breitbard%20told%20Business%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgap-company-history-rise-and-fall-pictures-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehe's%20been%20focused%20on%20restoring%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20brand's%20relevance%2C%20and%20part%20of%20that%20has%20included%20stripping%20away%20bureaucracy%20and%20unnecessary%20layers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeetings%20are%20often%20viewed%20as%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20corporate%20bureaucracy%2C%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Breitbard%20said%20he%20follows%20three%20rules%20to%20keep%20them%20in%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226239d9a7-37e6-4965-89a4-99d03679114b%5C%22%3EThe%203%20rules%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBreitbard%20said%20that%20if%20no%20one%20is%20sure%20why%20a%20recurring%20meeting%20is%20happening%2C%20it%20should%20be%20examined%20critically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20a%20default%20meeting%2C%20like%20it%20happens%20every%20single%20week%2C%20then%20I%20feel%20like%20we%20need%20to%20question%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Breitbard%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20second%20rule%20is%20to%20keep%20the%20invite%20list%20tight.%20Breitbard%20said%20it's%20a%20red%20flag%20when%20he%20walks%20into%20a%20meeting%2C%20and%20someone%20asks%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20are%20you%20in%20this%20meeting%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20ask%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20'no.'%20I%20clearly%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20here%20if%20you%20have%20to%20ask%2C%26quot%3B%20Breitbard%20said%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20meeting%20shouldn't%20be%20so%20big%20that%20people%20are%20invited%20without%20having%20a%20clear%20purpose%20for%20attending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20third%20habit%20rule%20is%20to%20end%20on%20time%20%E2%80%94%20or%20early.%20He%20said%20when%20it's%20near%20the%20end%20of%20a%20meeting%2C%20there%20often%20comes%20a%20time%20when%20people%20say%20something%20along%20the%20lines%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20we%20have%20five%20more%20minutes%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20five%20more%20minutes%2C%26quot%3B%20Breitbard%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20done%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreitbard%20said%20that%20people%20often%20book%2030-minute%20meetings%2C%20but%20he's%20inclined%20to%20finish%20earlier%20if%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20discussion%20has%20been%20accomplished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20minute%2024%2C%20I%20say%2C%20'OK%2C%20good%2C%20this%20was%20great.%20Thanks%2C%20everyone%2C'%26quot%3B%20Breitbard%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20when%20people%20question%20if%20it's%20really%20time%20to%20end%2C%20he%20says%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20we%20got%20what%20we%20needed.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e514236c-d7ff-42de-9b7e-757cad0505af%5C%22%3ECutting%20down%20on%20meetings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20over%20meetings%20and%20how%20they%20should%20be%20run%20isn't%20new.%20In%202018%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-productivity-tips-for-tesla-employees-2018-4%23large-format-meetings-waste-peoples-time-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elarge%20meetings%20should%20be%20scrapped%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20kept%20%26quot%3Bvery%20short%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20billionaire%20investor%20Mark%20Cuban%20has%20similarly%20said%20they%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20his%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20today's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-employees-prove-productivity-rto-performance-reviews-ai-investments-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresults-driven%20work%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20push%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20in%20meetings%20in%20has%20taken%20on%20a%20new%20form%20of%20urgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnowflake-ceo-shares-rules-for-meetings-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESnowflake%20CEO%20Sridhar%20Ramaswamy%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20December%20that%20%26quot%3Bmeetings%20are%20like%20bureaucracies%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20has%20four%20rules%20for%20managing%20his%20own%2C%20which%20involve%20keeping%20gatherings%20short%2C%20ensuring%20there's%20a%20purpose%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20there's%20an%20agenda%20and%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-chief-adam-mosseri-announces-five-day-office-return-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EInstagram%20chief%20Adam%20Mosseri%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20recently%20announced%20that%20recurring%20meetings%20would%20be%20canceled%20every%20six%20months%20and%20only%20re-added%20if%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20necessary.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20encouraged%20making%20recurring%20one-on-ones%20biweekly%20%26quot%3Bby%20default%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20workers%20should%20decline%20meetings%20that%20interfere%20with%20%26quot%3Bfocus%20blocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgap-brand-ceo-rules-for-meetings-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771583701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995c447f8731049f3af4d35%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgap-brand-ceo-rules-for-meetings-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Breitbard%2C%20CEO%20of%20Gap's%20global%20brand%2C%20said%20he%20questions%20recurring%20meetings%20and%20looks%20to%20end%20discussions%20early%20whenever%20possible.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgap-brand-ceo-rules-for-meetings-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PwC%20engineers%20built%20an%20AI%20agent%20to%20tackle%20the%20corporate%20world's%20least%20sexy%20task%3A%20spreadsheets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22PwC%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995ca36e1ba468a96ac36bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPwC%2C%20like%20many%20consulting%20firms%2C%20is%20investing%20heavily%20in%20engineering%20talent.%3Cp%3EArtur%20Widak%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPwC's%20engineers%20have%20created%20a%20new%20AI%20agent%20to%20tackle%20enterprise-grade%20spreadsheets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpreadsheets%20are%20unsexy%2C%20but%20crucial%20to%20corporate%20operations%2C%20PwC%20exec%20Matt%20Wood%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETraditional%20AIs%20%26quot%3Bjust%20kind%20of%20shrug%20and%20give%20up%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20meet%20a%20big%20spreadsheet%2C%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20way%20to%20judge%20a%20company's%20AI%20expertise%20isn't%20in%20the%20flashy%20headlines%2C%20but%20by%20looking%20at%20the%20%26quot%3Bunsexy%26quot%3B%20work%20rolling%20out%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20Matt%20Wood%2C%20PwC's%20global%20and%20US%20commercial%20technology%20and%20innovation%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Wood's%20theory%20holds%20%E2%80%94%20that%20real%20AI%20prowess%20shows%20up%20in%20unglamorous%20advances%20%E2%80%94%20PwC's%20latest%20launch%20is%20certainly%20notable.%20After%20all%2C%20what%20could%20be%20less%20sexy%20than%20spreadsheets%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-four-pwc-cuts-offices-offer-entry-level-consulting-jobs-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Four%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20this%20week%20that%20it%20has%20developed%20a%20%26quot%3Bfrontier%20AI%20agent%26quot%3B%20capable%20of%20reasoning%20over%20vast%2C%20enterprise-grade%20spreadsheets%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20conventional%20AI%20systems%20struggle%20with%20because%20of%20their%20complexity%2C%20size%2C%20and%20interdependencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agent%20can%20understand%20and%20navigate%20spreadsheets%2C%20mimicking%20%26quot%3Bhow%20experienced%20practitioners%20work%3A%20scanning%2C%20searching%2C%20jumping%20across%20tabs%2C%20integrating%20charts%20and%20receipts%2C%20and%20reasoning%2C%26quot%3B%20PwC%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201b63bee-2144-4b17-85da-03bb8708abd9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20spreadsheets%20matter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWood%2C%20who%20joined%20PwC%20in%202024%20from%20a%20role%20as%20vice%20president%20of%20AI%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-engineers-grate-against-internal-limits-claude-code-kiro-ai-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20when%20he%20started%2C%20he'd%20noticed%20the%20wraparound%2C%20ultra-wide%20monitors%20filled%20with%20spreadsheets%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20all%20anybody%20was%20working%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20were%20not%20%26quot%3Byour%20school%20soccer%20team%20budget%20spreadsheet%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wood.%20The%20spreadsheets%20that%20power%20large%20enterprises%20are%20enormously%20complex%2C%20often%20containing%20millions%20of%20cells%2C%20charts%2C%20graphs%2C%20images%2C%20receipts%2C%20and%20dozens%20of%20interlinked%20workbooks.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20more%20like%20financial%20engines%20than%20they%20are%20spreadsheets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20files%20often%20underpin%20business-critical%20decisions%2C%20yet%20PwC%20%26quot%3Bfound%20that%20even%20today's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-consulting-firms-mckinsey-pwc-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emodern%20AI%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20very%20poorly%20suited%20to%20managing%20these%20big%20enterprise%20spreadsheets%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20just%20kind%20of%20shrug%20and%20give%20up%20for%20want%20of%20a%20better%20word.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22952%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matt%20Wood%2C%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995cec2f8731049f3af4e30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Wood%2C%20PwC's%20global%20and%20US%20commercial%20technology%20and%20innovation%20officer.%3Cp%3EPwC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20an%20AI%20capable%20of%20understanding%20and%20reasoning%20across%20large%2C%20complicated%20spreadsheet%20applications%20is%20what%20PwC's%20engineers%20set%20out%20to%20solve.%20Their%20solution%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bgenuine%20advance%20in%20the%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agent%20has%20unlocked%20use%20cases%20across%20assurance%2C%20advisory%2C%20and%20tax%2C%20and%20boosts%20time%20saving%20on%20some%20tasks%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20literally%20days%20to%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-ai-training-changing-the-job-accountants-jenn-kosar-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaudit%20walkthroughs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20teams%20previously%20spent%20weeks%20manually%20gathering%20and%20validating%20evidence%20across%20numerous%20complex%20spreadsheets%20that%20existing%20AI%20tools%20couldn't%20handle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20users%20simply%20upload%20the%20files%2C%20and%20the%20frontier%20agent%20automatically%20maps%20their%20structure%2C%20extracts%20relevant%20data%2C%20and%20performs%20validation%20and%20consistency%20checks%20%E2%80%94%20tasks%20that%20would%20otherwise%20require%20combing%20through%20millions%20of%20rows%20by%20hand.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20faster%20meetings%2C%20less%20back-and-forth%20with%20clients%2C%20and%20cleaner%2C%20structured%20data%20ready%20for%20deeper%20AI-driven%20analysis%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227679577f-c4d8-4a28-b941-66d137015d55%5C%22%3EConsulting%20powered%20by%20engineers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPwC's%20AI%20spreadsheet%20agent%20was%20built%20in-house%20by%20engineers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20function%20the%20firm%20has%20been%20rapidly%20expanding%20as%20it%20shifts%20beyond%20the%20traditional%20roles%20associated%20with%20the%20Big%20Four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20PwC%20launched%20a%20dedicated%20tech%20engineering%20career%20track%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-big-four-rolls-out-new-engineering-career-path-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattract%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-big-four-rolls-out-new-engineering-career-path-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20more%20technical%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20it%20wants%20to%20become%20%26quot%3Ba%20destination%20for%20top%20engineering%20talent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20the%20firm%20offered%20only%20consulting%20and%20accounting%20career%20paths.%20Wood%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20adding%20the%20engineering%20track%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20signpost%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20future%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20PwC%20is%20retraining%20non-technical%20employees.%20The%20US%20branch%20of%20the%20firm%20recently%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-training-employees-for-ai-workplace-learning-agents-big-four-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompanywide%20workplace%20learning%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20focused%20on%20knowledge%20sharing%20and%20on%20developing%20a%20mix%20of%20human%20and%20AI%20skills%20needed%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWood%20described%20the%20work%20engineers%20do%20at%20PwC%20as%20having%20two%20modes%3A%20%26quot%3Btransforming%20today%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20for%20tomorrow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20focuses%20on%20improving%20current%20workflows%20%E2%80%94%20reducing%20back-and-forth%20with%20clients%2C%20increasing%20trust%2C%20and%20delivering%20work%20more%20efficiently.%20The%20second%20reimagines%20professional%20services%20from%20scratch%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20to%20start%20from%20a%20blank%20piece%20of%20paper%2C%20what%20would%20professional%20services%20look%20like%20in%20an%20AI%20agent%20world%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Wood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPwC%20engineers%20also%20work%20directly%20on%20client%20engagements%2C%20building%20AI%20systems%20tailored%20to%20specific%20projects.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20help%20organizations%20reorganize%20and%20redesign%20their%20finance%20functions%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20using%20agents%2C%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20consulting%20industry's%20top%20players%20are%20pursuing%20similar%20investments%20in%20technical%20talent%20as%20AI%20reshapes%20the%20work%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccenture%2C%20already%20one%20of%20consulting's%20most%20technically%20sophisticated%20players%2C%20has%20added%20nearly%2040%2C000%20AI%20and%20data%20professionals%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20They%20now%20account%20for%20roughly%2010%25%20of%20its%20global%20headcount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEY%2C%20another%20Big%20Four%20firm%2C%20has%20added%2061%2C000%20technologists%20since%202023%2C%20according%20to%20its%20latest%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Apthompson%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Epthompson%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20Polly_Thompson.89.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20here's%20our%20guide%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Esharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-engineers-launch-ai-agent-enterprise-grade-spreadsheets-big-four-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771583609000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995ce49e1ba468a96ac373b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-engineers-launch-ai-agent-enterprise-grade-spreadsheets-big-four-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20tech%20exec%20Matt%20Wood%20arrived%20at%20PwC%2C%20he%20found%20that%20massive%20spreadsheets%20were%20%26quot%3Ball%20anybody%20was%20working%20on.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40businessinsider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpwc-engineers-launch-ai-agent-enterprise-grade-spreadsheets-big-four-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Asos%20co-founder%20dies%20after%20Thailand%20apartment%20block%20fall%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771583564000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F5b0a%2Flive%2F49b53ef0-0e30-11f1-9972-d3f265c101c6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fce8w0n061ryo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Quentin%20Griffiths%20co-founded%20Asos%20in%202000%20and%20remained%20a%20significant%20shareholder%20after%20leaving%20the%20firm%20five%20years%20later.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A49%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fce8w0n061ryo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%203-fund%20portfolio%2C%20a%20no-kid%20lifestyle%2C%20and%20a%20'die%20with%20zero'%20mindset%3A%20How%20one%20NYC%20couple%20is%20retiring%20in%20their%2040s%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alex%20josette%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699773fce1ba468a96ac577a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22481%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinancially%20independent%20couple%20Josette%20Chang%20and%20Alexander%20Nathanson%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Josette%20Chang%20and%20Alexander%20Nathanson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJosette%20Chang%20and%20Alexander%20Nathanson%20paid%20off%20their%20mortgage%20early%20and%20hit%20financial%20independence%20in%20NYC.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20couple%20has%20a%20simple%20investment%20approach%20and%20embraces%20a%20%26quot%3Bdie%20with%20zero%26quot%3B%20financial%20mindset.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey've%20also%20avoided%20lifestyle%20creep%20and%20are%20intentional%20with%20how%20they%20spend%20their%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Nathanson%20always%20wanted%20to%20live%20in%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20to%20Manhattan%2C%20you've%20made%20it%20in%20New%20York%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Brooklyn%20native%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20and%20Josette%20Chang%20married%20in%202018%2C%20they%20fulfilled%20that%20dream%20by%20buying%20an%20apartment%20together%20in%20Midtown%20East.%20Beyond%20the%20personal%20significance%20for%20Nathanson%2C%20the%20purchase%20also%20made%20financial%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChang%2C%20who%20had%20been%20renting%20in%20New%20York%20since%20moving%20there%20for%20graduate%20school%2C%20was%20tired%20of%20the%20annual%20rent%20hikes.%20%26quot%3BI%20realized%2C%20'Wow%2C%20this%20is%20only%20going%20to%20go%20up.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20went%20from%20pricey%20New%20York%20City%20rent%20to%20a%20monthly%20mortgage%2C%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20to%20an%20incredibly%20low%20housing%20payment%20when%20they%20paid%20off%20their%20mortgage%20early%20in%202024.%20For%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20their%20only%20housing%20expense%20has%20been%20the%20monthly%20maintenance%20fee%20that%20comes%20with%20co-op%20living.%20Business%20Insider%20reviewed%20public%20records%20filed%20with%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Register%20that%20confirm%20the%20couple's%20mortgage%20was%20paid%20off%20in%20September%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20year%2C%20Chang%20quit%20her%20finance%20job%20and%20began%20early%20retirement.%20Nathanson%2C%20a%20physician%20specializing%20in%20obesity%20medicine%2C%20scaled%20back%20his%20hospital%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20February%202026%2C%20the%20financially%20independent%20couple%20comfortably%20lives%20off%20Nathanson's%20part-time%20salary.%20They%20could%20draw%20from%20their%20investment%20portfolio%20if%20needed%2C%20but%20they%20haven't%20had%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEliminating%20their%20mortgage%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20reaching%20that%20flexibility.%20So%20did%20earning%20high%20incomes%20and%20avoiding%20significant%20debt%20early%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENathanson%20said%20he%20paid%20off%20a%20relatively%20modest%20amount%20of%20student%20loans%20after%20attending%20medical%20school%20in-state.%20Chang%20had%20no%20student%20debt%20and%20was%20able%20to%20save%20aggressively%20in%20her%2020s%20while%20working%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20living%20with%20her%20parents%2C%20keeping%20her%20expenses%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20acknowledge%20our%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20Nathanson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20two%20high-income%20professionals%2C%20but%20even%20then%2C%20I%20still%20feel%20like%20more%20people%20can%20do%20it%20than%20may%20realize%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20path%20to%20financial%20independence%20wasn't%20built%20on%20stock%20picking%20or%20rental%20properties.%20Instead%2C%20it%20came%20down%20to%20a%20few%20deliberate%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8eb06b2-ea7f-4b2e-a1f8-c71f01149062%5C%22%3E1.%20Simplified%20investing%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20hiring%20a%20financial%20planner%2C%20Chang%20and%20Nathanson%20were%20saving%2C%20but%20without%20a%20clear%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20kind%20of%20on%20autopilot%2C%26quot%3B%20Nathanson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20have%20a%20clear%20strategy%20in%20mind.%20The%20internet%20says%2C%20'Max%20out%20your%20401(k).'%20We%20did%20that%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20really%20think%20much%20beyond%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20their%20portfolio%20is%20intentionally%20simple%2C%20consisting%20of%20just%20three%20low-cost%20index%20funds%3A%20a%20total%20US%20stock%20market%20fund%2C%20a%20total%20international%20stock%20market%20fund%2C%20and%20a%20total%20bond%20market%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20deliberately%20avoided%20more%20speculative%20investments%2C%20such%20as%20individual%20stock%20picking%20and%20cryptocurrency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20feel%20those%20types%20of%20investments%20have%20less%20track%20record%20and%20a%20higher%20risk%20profile%2C%26quot%3B%20Chang%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20point%20we%20are%20in%20our%20lives%2C%20we're%20comfortable%20relying%20on%20the%20historical%20performance%20of%20index%20funds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22nathanson%20chang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69977fb1a645d1188189a235%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENathanson%20and%20Chang%20reside%20in%20Midtown%20Manhattan.%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Nathanson%20and%20Josette%20Chang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22942f2ac2-6d86-4289-ad5a-ed784aa6c51e%5C%22%3E2.%20A%20child-free%20life%20and%20%26quot%3Bdie%20with%20zero%26quot%3B%20mindset%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple's%20financial%20plan%20is%20also%20shaped%20by%20their%20decision%20not%20to%20have%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20plan%20to%20have%20a%20large%20estate%20that%20we%20want%20to%20pass%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Nathanson%20said.%20They've%20completed%20estate%20and%20long-term%20care%20planning%20with%20the%20understanding%20that%20they%20won't%20have%20children%20as%20default%20caregivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20like%20the%20'Die%20With%20Zero'%20approach%3A%20Use%20the%20money%20when%20you%20can.%20There's%20no%20point%20in%20continuing%20to%20accumulate%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20Bill%20Perkins'%20book%2C%20which%20encourages%20prioritizing%20life%20experiences%20over%20endlessly%20growing%20a%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20them%2C%20financial%20independence%20isn't%20about%20building%20the%20biggest%20possible%20net%20worth.%20It's%20about%20having%20the%20flexibility%20to%20spend%20intentionally%20on%20experiences%20and%20priorities%20that%20matter%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Nathanson's%20part-time%20income%20means%20they%20aren't%20currently%20drawing%20from%20their%20investments%2C%20they%20know%20they%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20the%20math%20and%20realized%20we%20can%20start%20spending%20it%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIronically%2C%20we're%20not%20doing%20that%20yet%20because%20I'm%20still%20working%2C%20but%20I'm%20doing%20that%20not%20out%20of%20necessity.%20It's%20because%20it's%20what%20I%20want%20to%20be%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a954bd39-9d9e-41d3-987a-1c9e6133d054%5C%22%3E3.%20Avoiding%20lifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEarning%20two%20professional%20salaries%20in%20New%20York%20City%20can%20create%20pressure%20to%20spend%20accordingly.%20For%20Nathanson%20and%20Chang%2C%20avoiding%20lifestyle%20inflation%20has%20been%20central%20to%20reaching%20financial%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20income%20goes%20up%2C%20we%20try%20to%20be%20intentional%20about%20what%20we%20spend%20money%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nathanson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20nearly%20upgraded%20to%20a%20larger%20apartment%2C%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20it.%20%26quot%3BWe%20looked%20at%20bigger%20places%20and%20really%20thought%20about%20it%3A%20'Do%20we%20need%20to%20sell%20our%20current%20place%20just%20to%20move%20into%20a%20slightly%20bigger%20one%20in%20the%20same%20neighborhood%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20decided%20the%20answer%20was%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoving%20up%20would%20be%20just%20riding%20the%20hedonic%20treadmill%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20a%20bigger%20place%20now%2C%20and%20a%20few%20years%20later%20you'll%20want%20a%20bigger%20place%20again.%20We%20consciously%20decided%20to%20get%20off%20that%20treadmill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChang%20added%20that%20mindset%20plays%20a%20huge%20role%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20city%20like%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BComparison%20is%20the%20thief%20of%20your%20joy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20live%20here%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20what%20everyone%20else%20is%20doing%2C%20especially%20on%20social%20media.%20But%20it's%20important%20to%20stay%20on%20course%20and%20remember%20why%20you're%20doing%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20them%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20was%20work%20optionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIdentify%20what's%20important%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Nathanson%20said.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20on%20autopilot.%20Don't%20make%20decisions%20just%20because%20that's%20what%20everyone%20around%20you%20is%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-independence-in-new-york-city-early-retirement-investment-portfolio-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771583401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699773fce1ba468a96ac577a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-independence-in-new-york-city-early-retirement-investment-portfolio-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWe%20like%20the%20'Die%20With%20Zero'%20approach%3A%20Use%20the%20money%20when%20you%20can.%20There's%20no%20point%20in%20continuing%20to%20accumulate%20forever.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-independence-in-new-york-city-early-retirement-investment-portfolio-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saudi%20Arabia%3A%20King%20Salman%20orders%20disbursement%20of%20SAR3%20billion%20in%20Ramadan%20aid%20for%20households%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771583383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-128603647%2Cimgsize-389517.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fsaudi-arabia-king-salman-orders-disbursement-of-s